lenses-description =
    FreeSynergy Lenses is the information aggregator for the FreeSynergy platform.

    It queries all connected services — wiki, chat, task trackers, git repositories,
    maps, and calendars — through the message bus and presents the results in a
    unified view. One search, all services.

    Lenses is display-only. It shows summaries and links back to the original
    service but never modifies data. Automation and workflows live in Tasks.

lenses-features =
    - Aggregated search across all connected services
    - Per-service result sections: wiki, chat, tasks, git, map, calendar
    - Summary cards with a link to the original source
    - Personal lenses: save custom views and filters
    - Real-time updates via message bus subscriptions
    - Works offline with cached data from the last sync
